deck: Criminal Psychologist and Nemesis of Evil
description:
Origin

Lance Storm is a criminal psychologist who made a career tracking down and defeating a criminal master mind known as Professor Zorn. He retired after the final and real death of Zorn.
name: Lance Storm

deck: The only thing greater than his genius was his evil.
description:
Origin

Professor Zorn (sometimes Zarno), no first name or school where he got his professorship from is ever revealed, was an evil genius who turned his brilliance to murder, mayhem and evil.

His schemes ranged from blackmail, to cult murders, to the creations of killer “devil-doll” robots to the turning of a man into a super strong rampaging monster.

All his plots however were foiled by Lance Storm, criminal psychologist.
name: Professor Zorn

deck: Chuck is a high school jock who, with his friend Ted Chance Jr., drugged and raped Janey Belle and her friend Trish.
description:
Origin

Chuck Busey had been a high school jock, mostly hanging out with his friend Ted Chance, Jr. They had asked high school girls Janey Belle and Trish out for a party, where they drugged the girls and raped them. Years later, Chuck had married his high school girlfriend Sissy Green, found forgiveness in the heart of the Lord and became a local minister and church counselor.

After meeting Janey again, he tried to make amends. Inviting her over for dinner, Janey attacked and tortured Chuck, making his wife kill him.

deck: A strange inter-breed animal friend to the Plants and their allies.
description:
Twister is a "Truffle-Snuffle," a rare Guatemalan Pig-Dog...unless she is a Dog-Pig.

She assists Crazy Dave, Patrice, Nate, and the Plants against the Zombies.

Origin

Crazy Dave wins Twister in a bard game (where bards compete to sing the best songs) in Guatemala. She and Dave had a variety of experiences together, including challenging warrior mermaids and discovering the Boom Boom Mushroom.

Major Story Arcs

Zomboss threatens to drop the entire town of Neighborville into the caverns below, using a hydraulic elevator. Crazy Dave enlists Twister's help in finding the Boom Boom Mushroom, which can destroy the hydraulics.

Twister leads the kids underground and through a variety of adventures. She is a key part of the journey, finding the objects necessary to pass a dangerous river, knocking out a gargantuar, and ultimately reversing the elevator's direction, which brings the zombies up to the surface where they can be destroyed, rather the other way around.
